Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.consumer

This package holds all basic throwing Consumers.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ThrowingConsumer0
    Represents an operation that accepts no arguments and returns no result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingConsumer1<T1>
    Represents an operation that accepts one argument and returns no result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingConsumer2<T1,T2>
    Represents an operation that accepts two arguments and returns no result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingConsumerN
    Represents an operation that accepts n arguments and returns no result or throws a throwable.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ThrowingConsumerN.Instance
    An instance of AbstractThrowingConsumerN which properly defines the arity of that particular consumer.

Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.consumer Description

This package holds all basic throwing Consumers. Some functional interfaces are specialized such that the type parameters are primitives with additional type prefixes.
